  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[A \\.continuation.of./ B]\nStates:\nwhen:\n. A is \\set\n. B is \\set\nthat:\n. allOf:\n  . B \\:subset:/ A\n  . forAll: b is \\set\n    where:\n    . b \"in\" B\n    then:\n    . forAll: a is \\set\n      where:\n      . a \"in\" A\n      then:\n      . if:\n        . a \\:precedes:/ b\n        then:\n        . a \"in\" B\nDocumented:\n. called: \"continuation\"\n. written: \"A? \\text{ is a continuation of } B?\"\n. description: \"A well ordered set $A$ is a continuation of a well ordered set $B$ when $B \\subseteq A$, $B$ is an initial segment of $A$, and the ordering of $B$ is preserved in $A$.\"\nId: \"5f1f1c55-e4ac-42ca-b69a-ea33008529c7\"",
